2011. Combining musical stylings of bands like All Time Low, Four Year Strong, Yellowcard and Mayday Parade, 1000 Miles of Fire brings together urgent, hard hitting, honest and emotional pop punk tracks that will make a meaningful connection with just about anyone. The band has released 2 EP's throughout the course of their career. February 2014 saw the release of their debut EP, Nonstop Disaster while September of 2014 saw the release of another EP, Dreaming of Fireworks. With energetic fan favorites like Katie, Dreaming of Fireworks and For You a Thousand Times Over, 1000 Miles of Fire makes sure every live performance is an unforgettable experience for each and every fan. Having played numerous shows at venues like D-Note, The Roxy Theater, Rocky Mountain Sound Garden, Herman's Hideaway, Moe's BBQ and Denver's own Marquis Theater, 1000 Miles of Fire has managed to accomplish a lot in their short three years of existance. This young trio has already shared the stage with national acts like Ever so Android, Post Season and Firestarter, as well as Colorado favorites like Surviving April, Shatterproof, The Coast is Ours and Defy You Stars. Originally consisting of founding members Andrew Elofson (Vocals, Guitar, Drums) and CJ Eckenrode (Bass, Vocals), 2015 saw the addition of guitarist, Alena Popovich, a skilled player who brought a flowing, unique style of playing to the table. The future holds much for 1000 Miles of Fire as they are currently recording their debut full length, produced by their friend Ben Pisano (Corsicana) in his home studio.
